<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Apple Juice</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>6-8 medium-sized apples, cored and sliced</li>
            <li>Water</li>
            <li>Optional: Sweetener of your choice (sugar, honey, maple syrup), to taste</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Apple</li>
            <li>Beverage</li>
            <li>Refreshing</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Place the sliced apples in a large pot.</li>
            <li>Add enough water to cover the apples.</li>
            <li>Bring the water to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for about 20-30 minutes or until the apples are soft.</li>
            <li>Remove from heat and let it cool slightly.</li>
            <li>Using a blender or food processor, blend the cooked apples until smooth.</li>
            <li>Strain the mixture through a fine-mesh sieve or cheesecloth to extract the juice. You can press the solids to extract more liquid.</li>
            <li>Taste the apple juice and add sweetener if desired, stirring until it dissolves.</li>
            <li>Chill the apple juice in the refrigerator.</li>
            <li>Serve cold over ice and enjoy your refreshing Apple Juice!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

